<h1>About</h1>

<p><a href="http://www.usalaries.com" class="muted">uSalaries</a> is a salary search tool for certain public universities.</p>

<p>
  This tool is made by <a href="http://www.vkareh.net" class="muted">Victor Kareh</a> using <a href="http://http://www.nodejs.org/" class="muted">node.js</ a>, <a href="http://expressjs.com/" class="muted">Express</a>, <a href="http://documentcloud.github.com/backbone/" class="muted">Backbone.js</a>, <a href="http://www.flotcharts.org/" class="muted">Flot</a>, and several other modules for data manipulation and display.
  The layout is composed using <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/" class="muted">Twitter Bootstrap</a> and uses some <a href="http://glyphicons.com/" class="muted">Glyphicons</a>.
  The website itself is hosted on <a href="http://www.nodejitsu.com/" class="muted">nodejitsu</a> and the data is hosted on <a href="http://www.cloudant.com" class="muted">Cloudant</a>.
</p>

<p>
  The display of this salary data is in accordance with each state's Freedom of Information Act.
  The data itself is downloaded from public sources and converted to its current format by means of <a href="http://tojson.org" class="muted">.toJSON().org</a>.
  The data has been processed to make it easier to use and display on this website, but it has not been altered otherwise.
  If you feel there are errors or mistakes on the data or its display, feel free to <a href="http://www.vkareh.net/contact.html" class="muted">contact me</a>.
</p>
